{"name": "unblob-native", "metadata": {"name": "unblob-native", "version": "0.1.5", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Performance-critical functionality for Unblob", "upload_time": 1730989652}, "documentation": ["# unblob-native\n\nLooking for Unblob? Check out at https://unblob.org.\n\nThis package holds performance-critical components of Unblob,\nan _accurate, fast, and easy-to-use_ **extraction suite**. It parses\nunknown binary blobs for more than 30 different _archive, compression, and\nfile-system formats_, **extracts** their **content recursively**, and **carves**\nout **unknown chunks** that have not been accounted for.\n\nUnblob is _free to use_, licensed with the _MIT license_. It has a\nCommand Line Interface and can be used as a Python library.\nThis turns unblob into the perfect companion for extracting, **analyzing**,\nand **reverse engineering firmware images**.\n\n## Development\n\nThis package is easiest to develop using [Nix](https://nixos.org). Refer to the\nrelevant section of [The Unblob Documentation](https://unblob.org/installation/#nix-package)\non how to install Nix.\n\nOnce ready, issue `nix develop`, and the required tools will be set-up for you.\n\nThe package is managed via [PDM](https://pdm.fming.dev/latest/). Just call `pdm\nall`, and it will execute the required check and test steps for you. Use `pdm\nrun --list` to see what commands are being executed.\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "python.unblob_native", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "python.unblob_native.__doc__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "tests.test_math", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "tests.test_math.test_shannon_entropy", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": {"name": "bytes", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bytes", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "entropy", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_math.test_chi_square_entropy", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": {"name": "bytes", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bytes", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "chi_square_value", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "tests.test_math.UNIFORM_DISTRIBUTION", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_math.NON_UNIFORM_DISTRIBUTION", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "tests.test_sandbox", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "tests.test_sandbox.test_unsupported_platform", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_sandbox.sandbox_path", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "tmp_path_factory", "type": {"name": "pytest.TempPathFactory", "xref": {"fqname": "pytest.TempPathFactory", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_sandbox.landlock_supported", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_sandbox.test_read_sandboxing", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "request", "type": {"name": "pytest.FixtureRequest", "xref": {"fqname": "pytest.FixtureRequest", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "sandbox_path", "type": {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "do